  "text": "The Node.js ESM loader and CJS-ESM interop is implemented across 19 files (16 JS + 3 C++). The entry flow starts at run_main.js where executeUserEntryPoint calls shouldUseESMLoader to detect ESM entry points. The core orchestrator is the ModuleLoader class in esm/loader.js which coordinates: (1) resolution via defaultResolve/moduleResolve/packageResolve in esm/resolve.js, (2) format detection via defaultGetFormat in esm/get_format.js, (3) source loading via defaultLoad/getSource in esm/load.js, (4) format translation via the translators map in esm/translators.js (supporting module, commonjs, commonjs-sync, json, wasm, builtin, and TypeScript variants), and (5) linking/evaluation via ModuleJob/ModuleJobSync/ModuleJobBase in esm/module_job.js. Custom loader hooks are managed by the Hooks class and HooksProxy in esm/hooks.js. The CJS-ESM interop bridge lives in cjs/loader.js with finalizeEsmResolution handling ESM package resolution from CJS contexts, and loadESMFromCJS enabling require() of .mjs files. The native binding is ModuleWrap (src/module_wrap.cc/h), a C++ class wrapping V8's Module API for compilation, instantiation, and evaluation of ESM source text modules. node_contextify.cc also uses ModuleWrap for host-defined options when compiling modules in vm contexts. Supporting files include module_map.js (module cache), formats.js (format constants), utils.js (shared utilities), assert.js (import assertions), initialize_import_meta.js (import.meta setup), create_dynamic_module.js (synthetic modules), and shared_constants.js.",
